    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. Let's clarify the legal terms without the goblin references. Indemnification in the context of an NDA means that you, as the Recipient, agree to compensate the Disclosing Party for any losses, damages, liabilities, or expenses they incur as a result of your breach or failure to fulfill your obligations under the agreement. This can include legal fees, settlements, or any other costs associated with your non-compliance.\n\nIf you violate the terms of the NDA, you could indeed be held personally liable for these costs. This means that if the Disclosing Party incurs any financial losses or legal expenses due to your breach, you would be responsible for covering those expenses. In some cases, if the losses are significant, this could potentially affect your personal savings or assets, depending on the terms of the agreement and the severity of the breach. It's crucial to understand the specific obligations and potential consequences outlined in the NDA to avoid any unintended personal liability.",
